data.description: Outstanding colonial in desirable Meadowwood allotment. This home has been lovingly cared for and has the space and flexibility for many buyers. The stunning kitchen received a major remodel approximately 8 years ago and includes solid wood cabinets, granite counters, an expansive island with breakfast bar and beautiful stainless steel appliances. There is a reverse osmosis water purifier and instant hot water dispenser at the sink. The stove is a JennAire range. There is a terrific 3 season sunroom overlooking a very private back yard which borders the former Chapel Hills golf course. The large first floor laundry doubles as a mud room as it is located directly off the garage entrance.  The formal dining room with french doors is the perfect place for any dinner gathering. The partially finished basement is a great gaming or additional living space. The basement has been plumbed for an additional bath. A complete home security system was installed spring 2023. This convenient location is mere minutes from I-90 for easy access for commuters. Location is also 5 miles from Historic Bridge St and Walnut beach and only 8 miles to Geneva on the Lake and Geneva State Park. A classic timeless center hall beauty for sure!
